rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> the update</a>,<a class=
=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-5" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !=
important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[5]</span>
</a>=C2=A0prepared by FTX=E2=80=99s advisers (Alvarez &amp; Marsal, Sulliva=
n &amp; Cromwell and Perella Weinberg Partners), which covers both recoveri=
es and explanation. I want to start with the explanation part. The <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30288429.269516/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMDkvYmFua21hbi1m=
cmllZC1zLWZ0eC1oYWQtYS1kZWF0aC1zcGlyYWwtYmVmb3JlLWJpbmFuY2UtZGVhbD9jbXBpZD1=
CQkQwMTE4MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldH=
RlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzAxMTgmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a=
319a23cBa5fc3a8a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"=
_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-b=
ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid;=
 background-color: #ccc;">  basic explanation</a> of <a href=3D"https://lin=
k.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30288429.269516/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21i=
ZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTItMTMvaG93LXRvLWRvLWZyYXVkLWF0LWE=
tZnV0dXJlcy1leGNoYW5nZT9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMTE4MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPW=
VtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzAxMTgmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduP=
W1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBec8ae74c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" it=
emscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decor=
ation: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000=
000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  what went wrong=
 at FTX</a>=C2=A0is that FTX loaned billions of dollars to=C2=A0Alameda Res=
earch, a trading firm founded and mostly owned by Bankman-Fried. Alameda lo=
st the money, rendering FTX insolvent. And now=C2=A0FTX=E2=80=99s advisers =
say that they=C2=A0=E2=80=9Chave uncovered the mechanics behind how Alameda=
 Research had the ability to borrow without collateral effectively unlimite=
d amounts from customers and how a small group of individuals had the abili=
ty [to] remove digital assets from the exchange without being recorded on t=
he exchange ledger.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That discussion is on slide 19:</p>
<div class=3D"body-image" style=3D"margin: 20px 0px;">
